<materialsCitation box="[2117,2563,2705,2734]" pageId="149" pageNumber="751">Sheko Forest, 1930 m, Ethiopia.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="149" pageNumber="751" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="149.[1980,2573,2666,3088]" pageId="149" pageNumber="751">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lavrenchenko" authorityYear="2003" box="[1980,2223,2744,2773]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Desmomys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="149" pageNumber="751" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yaldeni">Desmomys yaldeni</taxonomicName>
1s distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1980,2168,2779,2813]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Pelomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="149" pageNumber="751" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="harringtoni">D. harringtoni</taxonomicName>
by havingmore gracile dentition, shorter fur, and slightly longer tail that is not bicolored. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="149" pageNumber="751" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="751" startId="149.[1980,2152,2897,2931]" targetBox="[1369,1957,2671,3085]" targetPageId="149">
