<emphasis bold="true" box="[1980,2156,2897,2931]" pageId="149" pageNumber="751">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from Sheko Forest, in W Ethiopia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="150" lastPageNumber="752" pageId="149" pageNumber="751" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="149.[1980,2573,2666,3088]" lastBlockId="149.[1368,2570,3094,3167]" pageId="149" pageNumber="751">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1980,2260,2976,3010]" pageId="149" pageNumber="751">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 117-132 mm, tail 141-145 mm, ear 17-5-18 mm, hindfoot 27-29 mm; weight 45— 49 g. Furis short, sandy brown and black-flecked above, and grayish white below with a mid-ventral light orange band. Tail is relatively long (115% of head-body length),
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="149" pageNumber="751" startId="149.[93,123,3260,3285]" targetBox="[1369,1957,2671,3085]" targetPageId="149">
<paragraph blockId="149.[91,2568,3235,3483]" pageId="149" pageNumber="751">
